			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Del. Lionell Spruill has me wondering why he isn&#8217;t Governor of Illinois.  It&#8217;s all about the Benjamins, it seems.  After making headlines for endorsing Del. Brian Moran for Governor, and raking in $7,500 a month for the honor, he announced this week that he endorsed Jon Bowerbank for LG.</p>
<p>According to the <a href="http://voices.washingtonpost.com/virginiapolitics/2008/12/bowerbank_hires_spruill_spruil.html">Washington Post</a>, Spruill is getting the cashola on that nod as well.  Bowerbank&#8217;s campaign manager wasn&#8217;t even sure how much they are paying him (wouldn&#8217;t want to contradict any upcoming filings, eh?).</p>
<p>That just leaves one question.  Which Democrat for Attorney General will cough up the cash to &#8220;earn&#8221; Spruill&#8217;s support?</p>
