			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><del datetime="2008-12-09T04:42:19+00:00">Today is</del>Yesterday was the anniversary of Pearl Harbor, a terrible day in American history, whose conflict largely ended in devastating atomic attacks on Japan.  Makes me wonder in today&#8217;s world when would we use the nuclear option.  If a group of terrorists set off a dirty bomb, would we respond in kind?  If so, against who?  What if a country launched one against us?  What would be the best thing to do?  I truly hope that we never have to answer these questions but seeing how India and Pakistan tensions can bring them to the brink of war it is an issue we need to figure out.  </p>
<p>On a side note, want to give my thanks again to all those who serve.  I have the pleasure of working the military on a daily basis and I see first hand their hard work and commitments.</p>
